    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>A Warning to Remember</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Norman Kiell letter on April 25 comment warning that baby chicks and ducklings can be source of salmonella</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>The short article ''That Cuddly Duckling Can Make You Ill'' (April 25) reminded me of the warning G.I.'s received in World War II while in India. It was to remember the Four F's: food, fingers, flies and feces to avoid amebiasis and/or bacillary dysentery, especially were we to eat in a local food emporium. The Four-F warning was an easy mnemonic device to remember, for it was one way to get discharged from the military. No one, to my knowledge, ever used this method.</p>
        <p>NORMAN  KIELL  Long Beach, N.Y.</p>
      </block>
